# You will practice the following 
passing environment parameters to you containers.
- Run ubi-minimal:latest container and pass tow env varibales GREET TARGET
```bash
./01-run-container-env.sh
```
- Time to run youyr DB engine, run postresql with following env vars -e POSTGRES_USER=admin -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=spassword -e POSTGRES_DB=demo 
```bash
./02-run-db-container.sh
```
- Connect to the running db container using same env vars and create 'container' table in demo db
```bash
./03-connect-to-db.sh
```
- Connect to the running db container ans select rows from 'container' table and then stop the db container and prune it
```bash
./04-validate-and-clean.sh
```